During Down Syndrome Awareness Month, the article highlights the contributions that people with Down syndrome make to their families, communities, and the nation. It acknowledges the efforts of family members, caregivers, medical professionals, and advocates in ensuring that individuals with Down syndrome have fulfilling lives. The article emphasizes the commitment to promoting the health, well-being, and dignity of all individuals with Down syndrome, and empowering them to pursue independence, pride in work, and full participation in society. It also addresses the need to increase public awareness and dispel myths about the condition. The article condemns the discrimination and disregard for human life that still exist towards individuals with Down syndrome. It recognizes the approximately 250,000 Americans with Down syndrome as embodying the spirit of the nation and emphasizes the importance of valuing and cherishing their unique gifts.